1. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the use of a group of agents to collaboratively clean an expanding region, which falls under the domain of multiagent systems.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper specifically mentions the use of "ant robots" and discusses the robots' hardware and software specifications, which falls under the domain of robotics.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of algorithms to enable collaborative coverage of the expanding region, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an analytic lower bound for the minimal number of agents and minimal time required to clean the expanding region, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the problem of cleaning an expanding region in a stochastic dynamic environment, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
